"style\":\"padding:0px;\",\"_style\":\"field_63c58e07abc14\",\"id\":\"\",\"_id\":\"field_63c58f5259e75\",\"row_classes\":\"\",\"_row_classes\":\"field_63fce04310be4\",\"row_style\":\"\",\"_row_style\":\"field_63fce05810be5\",\"background_image_image_classes\":\"\",\"_background_image_image_classes\":\"field_64137f5e4e069_field_64245ea4e8d5b\",\"background_image_image_style\":\"\",\"_background_image_image_style\":\"field_64137f5e4e069_field_64245eb4e8d5c\",\"background_image_image\":\"\",\"_background_image_image\":\"field_64137f5e4e069_field_64245ebee8d5d\",\"background_image\":\"\",\"_background_image\":\"field_64137ee5e518d\",\"code_block\":\"\",\"_code_block\":\"field_650236497fc5a\",\"column_classes\":\"col-lg-12 text-left\",\"_column_classes\":\"field_642452af4b3d5\",\"column_style\":\"\",\"_column_style\":\"field_642452c34b3d6\",\"content\":\"Costilla County and the surrounding San Luis Valley area offers incredible outdoor recreation:\\r\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eMt Blanca hiking and 4x4 trails\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eSangre de Cristo Mountain Range\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eRio Grande National Forest\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eGreat Sand Dunes National Park\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eFishing Conejos and Rio Grande rivers\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eFishing and camping at dozens of crystal clear mountain lakes.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eHiking and backpacking on 100\'s of miles of trails.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\r\\nATTENTION AGENTS\\r\\n\\r\\nWe pay a 5% commission to any Buyer\'s Agent that sells this property. We are not a brokerage, but welcome any and all that would like to do business with Down To Earth Investments.\\r\\n\\r\\nKEY FEATURES\\r\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003e***Affordable price with direct dirt road access. Many properties in the area do not have direct access\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eLocated only 13 miles north of San Luis in beautiful Costilla County\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eThis property is only 5 miles from Highway 159\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eThis property is also only 35 miles from Alamosa\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eAlamosa is a full service city with good restaurants, a Walmart and a university.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eIn this subdivision you may apply to the state for a well permit - in some of the other Costilla County subdivisions, you must first purchase water rights or not be able to drill a well at all - be careful!\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eIf you\'re an outdoors person, you\'ll find plenty to do here. There\'s enough hiking, biking, hunting, backpacking and fishing opportunities in this part of Colorado to keep you busy for an entire lifetime!\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003eExtremely low property taxes could make this an excellent long-term investment.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eOur land company, Down to Earth Investments, is a relationship-driven organization that is family owned and operated. We take great pride in providing quality pieces of land at discount prices and have a long history of delivering on our promises.\\u003c/b\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cspan\\u003eHOW TO BUY THIS PROPERTY\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003eContact Adam Zwingler at 720-823-9806 to let him know you would like to buy the property. He will help you get set up to pay the down payment and document preparation fee.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003eDuring the checkout procedure, you will be prompted to provide your name as you want it listed on the paperwork, as well as your address, etc.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003eWithin two business days you will receive a Purchase Agreement, Contract for Deed (Land Contract), and Promissory Note in your email to e-sign. You can sign electronically on your computer or phone.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003eAny questions about what you can or cannot build and can or cannot do on the property should be directed to the Costilla County Planning and Zoning Department: 719-937-7668\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003eEverything we know about the property is listed here. The information provided is deemed reliable but not guaranteed. Please do your own due diligence. All property is sold as-is, where-is.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n \\t\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003eThe down payment and document fee are non-refundable, so please be certain the property and terms will suit your needs BEFORE making your payment.\\u003c/span\\u003e\\u003c/li\\u003e\\r\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cspan\\u003eADDITIONAL PROPERTY DETAILS:\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003ePrice:\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e \\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003e$6,995 (Cash Discou\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cb\\u003ent Price)  OR  $10,995 (Payments)\\u003c/b\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eDocument Fee: \\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003e$195\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eSize:\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003e 5 acres +/-\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eAddress:\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003e TBD Juarez Rd, Fort Garland CO 81133\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eCounty:\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003e Costilla\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eState:\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003e Colorado\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eAssessor\'s Parcel Number (APN): \\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003e70212880\\u003c/span\\u003e\\r\\n\\r\\n\\u003cb\\u003eLegal Description:\\u003c/b\\u003e\\u003cspan\\u003e Sangre de Cristo Ranches, Unit D, Block 72, Lot 849\\u003c/span\\u0